1. GitHub Pages (Free & Easy)
Steps:
Create a GitHub Repository:

Go to GitHub and create a new repository (e.g., portfolio-website).

Upload Your Files:

If using Git:

sh
Copy
Edit
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/portfolio-website.git
git push -u origin main
Alternatively, upload files manually via the GitHub web interface.

Enable GitHub Pages:

Go to Settings â†’ Pages â†’ Under Source, select main branch and save.

Your site will be live at: https://your-username.github.io/portfolio-website/ ðŸŽ‰